content:
 &ldquo;Sometimes you&rsquo;ll never know the value of a moment until it becomes a memory.&rdquo;
— Anonymous
Source: Unknown
&ldquo;There&rsquo;s no such thing as a painless lesson, they just don&rsquo;t exist. Sacrifices are necessary. You can&rsquo;t gain anything without losing something first. Although if you can endure that pain and walk away from it, you&rsquo;ll find that you now have a heart strong enough to overcome any obstacle. Yeah&hellip; a heart made Fullmetal.&rdquo;
— Edward Elric
Source: Fullmetal Alchemist Brotherhood
&ldquo;The power of one man doesn&rsquo;t amount to much. But, with whatever little strength I&rsquo;m capable of&hellip; I&rsquo;ll do everything humanly possible to protect the people I love, and in turn they&rsquo;ll protect the ones they love. It seems like the least we tiny humans can do for each other.&rdquo;
— Edward Elric
Source: Fullmetal Alchemist Brotherhood
&ldquo;It always seems impossible until it’s done.&rdquo;
— Nelson Mandela
Source: Unknown
&ldquo;Except&hellip; it&rsquo;s a terrible day for rain.&rdquo;
— Roy Mustang
Source: Fullmetal Alchemist Brotherhood
&ldquo;Life is barely long enough to get good at something so be careful what you get good at&rdquo;
— Rust Cohle
Source: True Detective
&ldquo;If the only thing keeping a person decent is the expectation of divine reward, then brother, that person is a piece of shit&rdquo;
— Rust Cohle
Source: True Detective
